### Ingredex API — REST Client (VS Code / JetBrains)
### Set variables, then run requests in order where a token is needed.

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8000
@token = paste-access-token-after-verify-otp
@refreshToken = paste-refresh-token-after-verify-otp
@scanId = 00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000

###############################################################################
### Health (public)
###############################################################################

### Health check — DB + Redis
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

### Root
GET {{baseUrl}}/

###############################################################################
### Auth (public except /me)
###############################################################################

### Send OTP — use your email
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/send-otp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "you@example.com"
}

### Verify OTP — paste OTP from email/logs; copy access_token → @token, refresh_token → @refreshToken
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/verify-otp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "you@example.com",
  "otp": "123456"
}

### Refresh — exchange refresh token for new access + refresh (rotation)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/refresh
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refresh_token": "{{refreshToken}}"
}

### Logout — Bearer access token; optional body revokes one refresh session, omit body to revoke all
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/logout
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refresh_token": "{{refreshToken}}"
}

### Current user (Bearer required)
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###############################################################################
### Scan (public)
###############################################################################

### Barcode lookup (Open Food Facts + cache)
POST {{baseUrl}}/scan/barcode
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "barcode": "3017620422003"
}

### OCR — Groq Vision (multipart). Replace path with a local JPG/PNG/WebP.
### If "< ./file" fails, use your client’s file picker or curl:
### curl -sS -F "file=@label.png" {{baseUrl}}/scan/ocr
POST {{baseUrl}}/scan/ocr
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----IngredexBoundary

------IngredexBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="label.png"
Content-Type: image/png

< ./label.png
------IngredexBoundary--

###############################################################################
### Analyze (JWT required)
###############################################################################

### Analyze ingredients (CrewAI + Groq)
POST {{baseUrl}}/analyze
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "product_name": "Example cereal",
  "ingredients": "Whole grain oats, sugar, salt, natural flavor, vitamin E (mixed tocopherols)."
}

###############################################################################
### History (JWT required)
###############################################################################

### Stats — counts by scan_type
GET {{baseUrl}}/history/stats
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### List scans
GET {{baseUrl}}/history?limit=20&offset=0
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Single scan — set @scanId from list response
GET {{baseUrl}}/history/{{scanId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Delete scan
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/history/{{scanId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
